
IoT-Based Smart Farm Environmental Condition Classification is a smart agriculture project.

It uses IoT sensors to monitor greenhouse environmental conditions.

Sensors collect data such as temperature, humidity, soil moisture, and light intensity.

The collected data is sent to a processing system or cloud platform.

A machine learning model analyzes the environmental data.

The system classifies the conditions as optimal or unsuitable for plant growth.

If conditions are not suitable, the system can automatically control devices.

Devices like irrigation systems, fans, and lights can be turned on or off.

This helps farmers monitor farms remotely and reduce manual work.

The main goal is to improve crop growth and enable smart greenhouse automation.